law.text:
The director of the Division of Emergency Management shall appoint a state coordinator of search and rescue, who shall:
Identify, inventory, and coordinate resources available for searches and rescues;
Investigate and apply for grants and other financial assistance for searches and rescues;
Maintain statistics regarding searches and rescues;
Coordinate assistance during searches and rescues;
Act as liaison with other states' operations involving searches and rescues;
Provide assistance, upon request, during searches and rescues;
Prepare a plan for searches and rescues;
Prepare and distribute publications relating to searches and rescues;
Establish, by administrative regulation, recommendations for organizations specializing in search and rescue, and certify organizations which meet those recommendations at the appropriate level;
Maintain a list of all certified organizations and resources;
Coordinate training in techniques of search and rescue; and
Coordinate requests for federal assistance with the Air Force Rescue Coordination Center.
